documentType: evidence inventory and chain of custody form
summary: This document is an FBI evidence inventory and chain of custody record for items seized on August 28, 2006, related to case 31E-MM-108062. It lists physical evidence including massage tables, CDs, rental agreements, and notes, and tracks the custody transfers of this evidence from Miami to New York over several years.

events.title: Evidence Seizure

locations: 345 South County Road P, Palm Beach, FL, 33480
keyFacts: Evidence was seized from a Palm Beach, Florida address on August 28, 2006, as part of case 31E-MM-108062.
Seized items included two massage tables (one peach, one green), multiple CDs, a Thrifty rental agreement, and a note from someone named Johanna.
The evidence was transferred from the Miami FBI office to the New York FBI office, indicating multi-district investigative activity.
The document is a formal chain of custody record, showing the evidence was handled and transferred multiple times between 2006 and at least 2020.
